            "id": "start",
            "text": "Suit up with lab coat, nitrile gloves, and splash goggles. In a ventilated area, use a 100 mL graduated cylinder to pour 100 mL of distilled water into a 250 mL beaker. Place a glass stir rod, a pH strip, and the 37% HCl bottle nearby. Always add acid to water.",
